* Privacy & Compliance First: Corporate intellectual property (IP), proprietary code snippets, and personally identifiable information (PII) must never escape the user's controlled cloud boundary. No data is used to train public LLM models.
* Frictionless Ubiquity: Intake must take less than 30 seconds via voice, mobile micro-journaling, or background webhooks.
* Extreme Rubric Flexibility: The database and parsing layer must mold to any organizational appraisal template (MBOs, OKRs, Competency matrices, or numerical scales).

