## 4. Technical Architecture Blueprint## 4.1 Hybrid Storage & Database Schema Strategy
To handle highly volatile company structures, a hybrid relational/document model is required. Postgres with the pgvector extension provides transactional integrity for operational logs while allowing loose JSON metadata storage for unique evaluation rubrics.

       ┌───────────────────────┐
       │     users / teams     │
       └───────────┬───────────┘
                   │ 1:N
       ┌───────────▼───────────┐
       │     journal_logs      │
       │ ───────────────────── │
       │  - id: UUID           │
       │  - reporter_id: FK    │
       │  - target_user_id: FK │
       │  - raw_text: TEXT     │
       │  - clean_text: TEXT   │
       │  - vectors: VECTOR    │
       │  - metadata: JSONB    │
       └───────────┬───────────┘
                   │ N:1 (Dynamic Virtual Mapping)
       ┌───────────▼───────────┐
       │   evaluation_rubrics  │
       │ ───────────────────── │
       │  - id: UUID           │
       │  - org_id: UUID       │
       │  - template: JSONB    │◄── Captures nested nested JSON
       └───────────────────────┘    (e.g., 5/Exceeds, 4/Meets keys)

